<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-06-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-06-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">560.M2/357: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hull</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                            the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-28T18:00:00+01:00">June 28,
                                1933—6 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received June 28—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>74. Your 73, June 27, 11 a.m. Have transmitted instruction to Berne in
                        phraseology suggested adding phrase “which had adhered” before “leads to the
                        conclusion”.</p>
                    <p>I shall at proper moment probably make some short statement on the
                        subject.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>